4 days in Manila was not enough! I had a memorable time celebrating and being reunited with my best friends and family. From attending meetings, networking, and training I had an amazing time and made memories with life long friends ❤️❤️❤️

Mahalo @hpbaldwinhs for letting me speak on the importance of overcoming self critical thoughts. @whatmakesyoufeel_beautiful had the chance to talk to students on where these negative thoughts come from and how to cope with them and overcome it! It doesn’t happen over night and it takes a lot of self awareness to realize why these thoughts occur. I am someone who couldn’t see my potential because a little voice in my head told me I could never be anything in life when I realized where it came from I worked on these thoughts to push forward and have the tenacity to go for my dreams ✨

The month of May is Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month!!

In light of Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month, I feel it is only appropriate that I honour my two grandmothers and papa who came from Asian descent - Vietnam and Philippines 

They bravely ventured out this beautiful country I was born in, to create a life and legacy for my family and I to pursue “the great American dream”. A land where all things are possible.

To know my heritage and be able to understand the sacrifices my grandparents made to migrate to America has provided me with the resilience, strength and tenacity to be able to pursue this journey of mine.

As Miss Hawaii USA, and a woman born from Asian heritage and descent, I hope to be a symbol and beacon of light for other Asian-Americans, for generations to come, to follow their hopes and dreams. Not just for our own personal pursuit, but for our families who sacrificed so much, to give us stepping stones for these opportunities. 🇵🇭🇺🇸🇻🇳

#asianamericanheritagemonth #aapiheritagemonth

Aloha, 
My heart breaks as I write this the past few days have been hard for the people of Maui. My home. We are coming together as a community helping as much as we can. The shelters are packed full of people who lost everything and have survived with nothing but the clothes on their backs. There are families, children, and the elderly at the shelters who need help and have no where to go. It would mean everything If we could spread the word and help donate to the Miss Hawaii USA foundation where 100% of the proceeds will be going to the families affected. The strength of our island and our people will overcome this adversity. Their strength during this time is my inspiration.

I announce with immense pleasure and gratitude that last night I took home the best costume award at Miss USA! @missusa This means so much more than a win to me and my home state, as this symbolises a beacon of hope, overcoming catastrophe and true resilience.

The banyan tree of Maui survived the worst fires in American history in over 100 years. This costume pays tribute to the roots of Hawaii and everlasting cycle of life showing the indomitable spirit of the people of Hawaii! 

This is for my state, my people and our home!

Today is the day of a once in a lifetime experience. My life changed when I decided to run for Miss Hawaii USA. The growth, self mastery, and purpose I have achieved during this journey is one I will forever be grateful for. 
Mahalo to my family, friends, supporters you were my rock and believed in me on days where I didn’t. I love you all!! 
To Hawaii, my home, my island I will walk across the Miss USA stage with you on my chest and heart 🌺

#misshiusa #missusa2023 #missusa #hawaii #reno #grandsierra #thedefinitionofpageantry

It’s been an absolute pleasure to go through this once in a lifetime experience, competing for Miss USA and having the privilege to win 1st runner up, best costume, and best interview.

This experience has enabled me to have a new found appreciation and respect for the competition, as I’ve first hand been through a transformative journey and experienced amazing growth. I cannot wait to embark on my next journey as I close this chapter. Stay Tuned!

I’ve met other amazing women and have been able to share memories that will last a lifetime. 

Thank You from the bottom of my heart to my family, partner, besties, supporters!!! You are my rock!! I love you all. 

Lastly, I want to congratulate the new Miss USA 2023 @noeliavoigt it was an honor to take the stage as final 2! 🇺🇸❤️
